{
  "text": "Dimethylamiloride. In other tissues it has been suggested that Na \u03e9 /H \u03e9 exchanger activity may be altered by ANG II. To examine the possible contribution of the Na \u03e9 /H \u03e9 exchanger to the ANG II-induced increase of NPE sodium content, cells were exposed to ANG II in the presence of 10 M dimethylamiloride (DMA), an inhibitor of Na \u03e9 /H \u03e9 exchange (6) that is also known to inhibit epithelial sodium channels when used at higher concentrations (5, [CITATION_1] . In the presence of DMA, ANG II failed to elicit a significant increase of cell sodium content (Fig. 1B) .",
  "correct_citation": {
